<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cardinals, Rockies Split Games  </HEADLINE>
By AARON J. LOPEZ, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   DENVER (AP) -- Jeff Manto hit a go-ahead double during an
eight-run sixth inning that propelled the Colorado Rockies to a
14-13 victory over the St. Louis Cardinals in the second game of a
split doubleheader Sunday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockies, who lost the afternoon opener 9-3, came back from
deficits of 3-0, 7-3 and 9-5 by sending 14 men to the plate against
four St. Louis pitchers in the sixth.
</P>
<P>
   The outburst came three days after Colorado scored 10 runs in
