<HEADLINE> Trinidad, Haiti and Cuba Advance  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Trinidad and Tobago advanced Sunday to the third
round of
Caribbean qualifying for the 2002 World Cup along with Haiti and
Cuba.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Nigel Pierre scored in the 72nd minute as Trinidad and Tobago
won 1-0 at the Dominican Republic to advance on 4-0 aggregate in
the home-and-home, total-goals series.
</P>
<P>
   Trinidad and Tobago faces Haiti, which advanced 13-0 following a
4-0 win at the Bahamas. Vladimir Edouard scored in the ninth and 50
minutes, and Gulman Pierre added goals in the 60th and 76th.
</P>
<P>
   Cuba advanced on 1-0 aggregate following a scoreless tie at
Suriname and plays Barbados. Barbados took a 3-1 lead into Sunday's
second leg, which was delayed by a power failure in Bridgetown,
Barbados, and advanced 7-1.
</P>
<P>
   In second-round, first-leg games Sunday, Bermuda played a
scoreless tie at Antigua and Barbuda, and St. Vincent and the
Grenadines beat visiting St. Kitts and Nevis 1-0 on Marlon James'
goal in the 82nd minute.
</P>
<P>
   In Central America's first round, El Salvador (3-0) won 3-1 at
Belize (0-3) in Group A and Honduras (2-1) won 1-0 at Nicaragua
(0-3). Belize and Nicaragua were eliminated with the losses.
</P>
<P>
   El Salvador got goals from Raul Diaz Arce of Major League
Soccer's Tampa Bay Mutiny in the fifth minute, from Elmer Martinez
in the 51st minute and from Jorge Rodriguez in the 64th minute.
Bent Burguess scored for Belize in the 66th minute
</P>
<P>
   Luis Ramirez scored for Honduras in the 70th minute at Diriamba.
</P>
</TEXT>
