<HEADLINE> Dow Up 60; Nasdaq Off 92  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices are mixed in early trading Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The Dow Jones Industrial Average is up 60 points. Losing issues
on the New York Stock Exchange hold a two-to-one lead over gainers.
</P>
<P>
   The Nasdaq Composite Index is off 92 points and the Standard &AMP;
Poor's 500 Stock Index is down five points.
</P>
<P>
   Analysts, in general, are looking for a choppy session, but
whether the popular averages finish up or down is anyone's guess.
</P>
<P>
   Overseas markets have been sharply lower across the board.
</P>
<P>
   Asian stocks showed the worst declines, having been closed while
Wall Street tumbled Friday.
</P>
<P>
   But there may be some reason for optimism, and it comes in the
form of strong earnings news.
</P>
<P>
   Several blue-chip companies have posted better-than-expected
earnings on Monday, including Citigroup, Ford, Bank of America and
Eastman Kodak.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices are modestly lower.
</P>
</TEXT>
