<HEADLINE> Northeast Gets Another Day To File  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Because April 15 fell on a Saturday, most Americans
have until
midnight tonight to get their federal income tax returns to a local
post office and postmarked without incurring a late penalty.
<TEXT>
<P>
   People in Massachusetts, Connecticut, Maine, New Hampshire,
Rhode Island, Vermont and most of New York outside of the New York
City area have another day -- until midnight Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
   The Internal Revenue Service decided to allow all those
Northeast filers an extra day because of the annual Patriot's Day
legal holiday in Maine and Massachusetts. Many of the returns from
the region are handled by the IRS service center at Andover, Mass.
</P>
<P>
   New York taxpayers from New York City and Nassau, Rockland,
Suffolk and Westchester counties have to file their returns by
midnight tonight.
</P>
