<HEADLINE> AP Financial News at 5:10 p.m. EDT  </HEADLINE>
Monday, April 17, 2000
<TEXT>
<P>
   Dow Ends Up 276; Record Nasdaq Gain
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Big-name stocks rallied back today, surging into
the close amid hopes Wall Street hit bottom in last week's
punishing selloff. Most other stocks fell again, however, as
bargain hunters remained leery of smaller companies. The battered
Nasdaq composite index jumped a record 217.68 points to 3,538.97,
nearly all of it coming over the final hour of trading. The Dow
Jones industrial average rose 276.74 to 10,582.51, recovering
nearly half of Friday's record one-day point drop of 617.78. But
while investors showed renewed interest in many of the big and
popular companies that tumbled last week, the bias remained
negative on the broad market, where declining issues outnumbered
advancers by nearly a 3-to-2 margin.
</P>
<P>
   Financial figures
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Financial Figures at the close:
Dow Industrials:        10582.51 + 276.74
NYSE Issues:         Advances 1285  Declines 1732  Unchgd  416
