<HEADLINE> Bank of America's Profits Rise  </HEADLINE>
By PAUL NOWELL, AP Business Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   CHARLOTTE, N.C. (AP) -- Bank of America Corp. said Monday its
profits climbed almost 17 percent in the first quarter as the
nation's second-largest bank benefitted from growth in securities
trading and investment banking.
</P>
<P>
   Charlotte-based Bank of America earned $2.24 billion, or $1.33 a
share, beating Wall Street's average estimate of $1.24 a share,
according to First Call/Thomson Financial.
</P>
<P>
   Bank of America earned $1.92 billion, or $1.08 a share, in the
first quarter last year.
</P>
<P>
   ''We are gaining market share in many investment banking
products as we meet more of our business clients' financial
needs,'' said Hugh L. McColl, chairman and chief executive officer.
''Our customer retention continues to improve, and we are having
good success in rewarding customers who bring more of their
business to our company.''
</P>
<P>
   A 26 percent jump in Bank of America's non-interest income more
than offset a 1 percent decline in net-interest income.
</P>
<P>
   Strong revenues from trading, investment banking and
underwriting fees pushed non-interest income to $4.05 billion from
$3.22 billion a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   The bank's net-interest income, however, was squeezed by
unfavorable interest-rate spreads between what the bank paid on
deposits and charged on loans. Net-interest income totaled $4.60
billion in the quarter, down slightly from $4.65 billion in the
year-ago period.
</P>
<P>
   Bank of America's stock rose 37{ cents to $50.31\ a share in
trading at 4:30 p.m. on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   McColl also noted that online banking enrollments increased to
125,000 per month, from a pace of 80,000 per month a year ago.
Total online retail customers rose to more than 2.1 million, he
said.
</P>
<P>
   Visitors to the bank's web site increased by more than 70
percent, and consumer loan products sold over the Internet
increased by 300 percent, the bank said in its earnings release.
</P>
<P>
   With $633 billion in assets and more than 4,500 branches in 21
states, Bank of America serves more than 30 million households and
2 million businesses.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   http://www.bankofamerica.com
</P>
</TEXT>
