<HEADLINE> Dominican Cops Find Hidden Cocaine  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SANTO DOMINGO, Dominican Republic (AP) -- Dominican police have
seized 150 pounds of cocaine hidden inside coconuts bound for New
Jersey, officials said Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Police at Santo Domingo's port detected the drugs as 265
coconuts were being readied to loading onto a freighter headed to
Elizabeth, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   Smugglers had cut open the coconuts with a saw, loaded them with
bags of cocaine and glued them back together, investigators said.
</P>
<P>
   They said they have detained 10 people connected with a fruit
export company that organized the shipment.
</P>
