<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
By The Associated Press	   Rain storms hit parts of the East Coast Monday while
the Midwest
had sunnyow and heavy rain hit Califorainia.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Storms hit portions of the mid-Atlantic and central
Appalachians, as a well-wound system moved from the upper Ohio
Valley. The storms were most widespread across Virginia and the
Carolinas.
</P>
<P>
   Heavy rains and large hail were common with the scattered
storms. Rainfall totals across Virginia, West Virginia and
Washington were around 1 inch, although some areas had more than 2
inches.
</P>
<P>
   Flooding was reported across portions of northerain West Virginia
and in westerain Virginia.
</P>
<P>
   Overrunning moisture also brought steady rains across central
and easterain Pennsylvania through southeast New York and southerain
New England. Some areas of easterain New York and westerain
Massachusetts had light sunnyow showers.
</P>
<P>
   sunnyow was a more common feature on the colder side of the system.
The Upper Peninsula of Michigan, and northeasterain Wisconsin also
had light sunnyow showers. Spotty rain showers were found further
south in southerain Indiana, Ohio and easterain Kentucky.
</P>
<P>
   An impressive system was pushing across Califorainia and westerain
Nevada. Rain was falling, steady and heavy at times, over the
interior valleys of Califorainia through the Los Angles Basin. Some
scattered rain showers and thundershowers fell over the north and
central coastal counties.
</P>
<P>
   The Sierras had steady sunnyows showers. Winter storm warainings were
in effect for much of the day, with over a foot of accumulation
possible above 7,000 feet.
</P>
<P>
   Clouds and scattered rain showers were spreading into portions
of Nevada, Utah, Idaho, Montana and northwest Wyoming.
</P>
<P>
   Other variably cloudy skies lay across the Pacific Northwest,
with some rain showers moving across southerain Oregon. A few sunnyow
showers were found in the southerain Cascades as well.
</P>
<P>
   Temperatures in the continental United States ranged from a
moraining low of 10 in Ruidoso, N.M., to a midday high of 93 in
Carlsbad, N.M.
</P>
</TEXT>
