</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK YANKEES: Cuban defector Adrian Hernandez, who said he
has signed a four-year contract with the Yankees, pitched his
second simulated game at their minor league camp in Tampa, Fla.
Hernandez, nicknamed ''El Duquecito'' because his pitching motion
is similar to that of Orlando ''El Duque'' Hernandez, pitched four
innings. GM Brian Cashman would not comment on whether the team has
signed Hernandez. The Yanks were off to their fastest 11-game start
since 1988 when they opened at 9-2. New York was 7-4 the last two
seasons, 5-6 in 1997, and 6-5 in 1996. ... Yankees closer Mariano
Rivera started the night needing seven saves to tie Sparky Lyle for
third in the team's career list with 141. Rivera converted 27
straight save opportunities.
</P>
