word of the postponement before it was scheduled to leave the
hotel. ... The Mariners went 8-4 against the White Sox in 1999 to
win the season series for the fifth straight year. ... Hitting
coach Gerald Perry was busy as the Mariners hit in the indoor
batting cages Monday. Included in the group were SS Alex Rodriguez,
DH Edgar Martinez and IF Mark McLemore.
NATIONAL LEAGUE:
Marlins-Cubs:	   FLORIDA: All the Florida Marlins want is a little love. Despite
a lineup filled with youngsters and little-knowns, the Marlins are
now 8-6 and a game ahead of Atlanta atop the NL East. But Pro
Player Stadium will probably still be empty when the Marlins return
home Tuesday. In the first series of the season, against San
Francisco, the Marlins drew 9,524, 8,365 and 7,741. ''When people
call us a Triple-A team, that's the biggest insult,'' manager John
Boles said. ''If we are, we're the best ever assembled. We want so
bad to be loved by the people of South Florida. We haven't been
accepted since the 1997.'' ... The Marlins' bullpen went the entire
seven-game road trip without giving up an earned run. ... 2B Luis
Castillo, who's missed the last two games with back pain, will have
a bone scan Tuesday after an MRI was inconclusive.
</P>
