ready for the majors, though, Baylor is going to use him no matter
where the Cubs are. ''If it's on the road, we can only alter our
pitching rotation somewhat,'' Baylor said. ''When he's ready,
believe me, I'm going to find him a spot to pitch.'' Wood,
recovering from ligament replacement surgery, will make another
rehabilitation start Tuesday with Single-A Dayton. He'll throw 100
pitches or seven innings, and could be ready to rejoin the Cubs as
early as May. ... Seen on the Cubs clubhouse message board: ''Be
sure to stretch your Gutierrez muscles.'' The Cubs shortstop didn't
play in Japan because of a strained muscle in his rib cage. ...
With their three-game road trip to Montreal that begins Tuesday,
the Cubs will be playing in their third country. Shane Andrews and
Mark Grace will be looking to homer in three different countries.
