<HEADLINE> Iraqi Defense Minister Visits Russia  </HEADLINE>
By WAIEL FALEH, Associated Press Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   BAGHDAD, Iraq (AP) -- Iraq's defense minister met in Moscow last
week with his Russian counterpart to discuss military cooperation,
the official Iraqi News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
   Russia's ITAR-Tass news agency also reported the visit, saying
Lt. General Sultan Hashim Ahmed made the stop in Moscow while
returning home from Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first official foreign trip by an Iraqi defense
minister since the end of the 1991 Gulf War. It wasn't immediately
clear why he visited the Yugoslav capital of Belgrade.
</P>
<P>
   Iraqi military cooperation with other countries has been a
sensitive subject given that Baghdad has been refusing for more
than a year to allow the United Nations to carry out inspections
for suspected weapons of mass destruction. Iraq is under an arms
embargo as part of U.N. sanctions imposed after its invasion of
Kuwait in 1990.
</P>
<P>
   Ahmed was in Russia from Friday to Sunday and met with Russian
Defense Minister Igor Sergeyev. INA said the two dealt with
''bilateral relations in military fields'' and ''the unjust
sanctions imposed on Iraq.'' It gave no other details.
</P>
<P>
   Russia is a staunch ally of Iraq in its efforts to have U.N.
sanctions lifted, in part because of the millions of dollars of
debts from the Soviet-era owed by Iraq. Iraq now pays Russia with
oil.
</P>
<P>
   The two countries have had military pacts since 1970, and the
Iraqi army uses almost entirely Russian weapons and machinery.
</P>
<P>
   Russian military experts had left the country days before the
Gulf War started in 1991, but returned later to maintain the Iraqi
military industry and what was left of the Iraqi air force.
</P>
<P>
   Ahmed was appointed defense minister just after the Gulf War. He
was the top military official who negotiated the cease-fire with
the U.S.-led allies on the Iraqi-Kuwaiti borders in March 1991.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-04-17-00 2214 </TRAILER>
