<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-17 23:27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spurs 100, Grizzlies 93  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- David Robinson scored 12 of his 27 points in
the fourth quarter to rally the San Antonio Spurs to a 100-93
victory over the Vancouver Grizzlies on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   San Antonio played its third straight game without Tim Duncan,
who has a left knee injury. The Spurs are 4-3 this season without
their All-Star forward.
</P>
<P>
   The win clinched at least the No. 5 playoff position in the
Western Conference for the Spurs, and moved them within a half-game
of Phoenix for the No. 4 slot. The Spurs have one regular season
game remaining, at home Wednesday against the Los Angeles Lakers.
</P>
<P>
   The Suns play at home Tuesday against Houston, and at Golden
State on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Avery Johnson scored a season-high 24 points, and Antonio
Daniels added 12 for the Spurs.
</P>
<P>
   Vancouver, loser of seven straight games, was led by Michael
Dickerson with 29 points. Shareef Abdur-Rahim had 27.
</P>
<P>
   Trailing 83-74 early in the fourth quarter, San Antonio rallied
with a 15-2 run to take an 89-85 lead on a Daniels 3-pointer with
5:19 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Vancouver went back up 91-90 on Dickerson's jump shot with 3:34
to play.
</P>
<P>
   San Antonio then took the lead for good on consecutive baskets
by Robinson and Daniels, the latter coming on a driving layup which
gave the Spurs a 94-91 advantage with 2:51 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   San Antonio, which has won five of six games, continued to pull
away, and two Johnson free throws made it 100-93 with 20 seconds
left.
</P>
<P>
   Held to only two points in the first half, Abdur-Rahim exploded
for 19 of Vancouver's first 21 points in the third quarter as the
Grizzlies grabbed a 74-62 lead with 3:31 to play in the third
quarter. He finished with 21 third-quarter points and Vancouver led
78-72 going to the fourth.
</P>
<P>
   Behind 10 points by Johnson, San Antonio closed the first
quarter with an 11-4 run to lead 28-25 after one.
</P>
<P>
   Dickerson had 21 first half points, on 7-of-10 shooting, as
Vancouver took a 53-50 halftime lead.
Notes: San Antonio is 30-10 at home. ... San Antonio swept the
four-game season series from Vancouver, and leads the teams'
all-time series 16-3. ... Vancouver is 3-22 since Feb. 26. ...
Vancouver point guard Mike Bibby added to his club season assist
record with seven against San Antonio. He has 657 this season.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
