<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico Declares Drought Emergency  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY (AP) -- The government has declared nine
drought-stricken states in northern Mexico disaster areas, clearing
the way for federal aid, the government news agency Notimex
reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
   States across northern Mexico have been suffering from prolonged
droughts and have experienced less than half of the average
rainfall, according to Notimex reports.
</P>
<P>
   Similar drought conditions spread across the region last year,
killing cattle, parching crops and forcing some communities to
truck in drinking water.
</P>
</TEXT>
